name: John Pesutto
summary: The Victorian opposition is in turmoil, with the leadership of John Pesutto under threat. Four MPs have requested a special meeting to vote on his future, following a series of disagreements. This includes the controversial readmission of MP Moira Deeming, which Pesutto has since backflipped on. The situation has been described as a "Jacinta's Christmas present," referring to the infamous Christmas Day spill of former leader Matthew Guy. Pesutto has vowed to stay on as leader, but there is growing anger within the party, with many MPs questioning his ability to unite the team. The latest vote on Deeming's readmission was blocked, further highlighting the divisions within the Victorian Liberals. The ongoing in-fighting is damaging the party's reputation, and it remains to be seen whether Pesutto can survive as leader.

name: Vanuatu earthquakes
summary: A devastating earthquake of magnitude 7.4 has struck Vanuatu, causing widespread damage and loss of life. At least 14 people have been killed and hundreds injured, with some still trapped in the rubble. Rescue efforts are underway, but the situation is dire as the island nation's health system is on the brink of being overwhelmed. The US Embassy has also suffered significant damage. As aftershocks continue to rattle the region, concerns are growing that the situation could worsen, with fears of disease outbreaks due to the lack of water and sanitation.
